        "body": "\u003cbr\u003eHi Vince\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cblockquote\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u0026gt;I only want Canadian IP to access the website and any whitelist IP that i can clear to access the site as developers. Can this be done ?? \u003c/span\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003c/blockquote\u003e\u003cbr\u003eIf you set up a lock for your store or the products in your store using Locksmith, you can then add multiple keys to that lock. The first key can restrict access based on a customer's location, and the second can be a separate key that grants access based on something else - like a signed in customer account that has a tag like \"admin\".\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eYou can check for a customer tag using the \"is tagged with...\" key condition. There is an IP address key condition that can check for specific IP addresses, but I wouldn't recommend this given that most ISPs use static IP addresses that will change over time.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eKeep in mind, the location key conditions can also be accessed using a VPN. So your developers could also change their connection location and access the storefront that way.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eIn your last message you said \"\u003cb\u003esome days its in the thousands , completely slowing down the website\u003c/b\u003e\". I'm not sure what this is about. Could you give me some context on what this is about?\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eCheers! :)\u003cbr\u003e-Tristan\u0026nbsp;\u003cbr\u003e",
