        "action": { "type": "default", "associatedEntities": {} },
        "body": "Just to make sure on the same page, you're looking to manage access to products in the Online Sales channel storefront, not in the Shopify admin?\u003cbr\u003eYes thats correct\u003cbr\u003eI only want Canadian IP to access the website\u003cbr\u003eand any whitelist IP that i can clear to access the site as developers\u003cbr\u003eCan this be done ??\u003cbr\u003eVince\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eLocksmith can help with managing access to products and resources in the Online Sales channels storefront. Locksmith can be used to lock individual products or collections of products, and there's a location key condition, or domain/market key conditions that can be used to grant or block access to customers based on the location they are connecting from. \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eI've included our guide on setting up a basic lock here, for reference: [ Creating locks ]( https://www.locksmith.guide/basics/creating-locks )\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThere are two ways to manage access your locks based on a customer's location:\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eWe have a location key condition - that checks the approximate location a customer is connecting from based on their IP address. Importantly, this will negatively affect SEO for locked content that isn't a variant, or using manual mode. Our guide on using this key condition is here: [ Restricting by a visitor's location ]( https://docs.uselocksmith.com/article/192-restricting-by-location )\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThe domain key or a Liquid key condition can be used to check for the market a customer is connecting from. This works with Shopify Markets in your store to either check the domain the customers are viewing. Or a Liquid lock can be used to check for a domain's subfolder, or the localisation object that the customer has been assigned. These keys won't prevent search engines from indexing that locked content for those regions: [ Showing content only to specific Markets ]( https://www.locksmith.guide/tutorials/more/shopify-markets )\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eIt's also worth noting here that Locksmith cannot restrict shipping locations. But Shopify does have some options for that: [ Shopify's shipping profiles ]( https://help.shopify.com/en/manual/shipping/setting-up-and-managing-your-shipping/shipping-profiles/setting-up-shipping-profiles#create-a-custom-shipping-profile )\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eLet me know if you have any questions about this. :)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eCheers!\u003cbr\u003e-Tristan\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eDid you get what you needed?    [ 👍 ]( https://secure.helpscout.net/satisfaction/708173258/record/7855708272/1/ )    [ 👎 ]( https://secure.helpscout.net/satisfaction/708173258/record/7855708272/3/ )\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e--\u003cbr\u003e 🔆 \u003cbr\u003e 🌱 [ Lightward AI ]( https://lightward.ai/ ) 🐉\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e We also made [ Mechanic ]( https://apps.shopify.com/mechanic )!{#HS:2611356506-79303#}",
