        "body": "Hi there!\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eTristan here from the Locksmith team. I hope you're well. :)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eJust to make sure on the same page, you're looking to manage access to products in the Online Sales channel \u003cspan\u003estorefront\u003c/span\u003e, not in the Shopify admin?\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eLocksmith can help with managing access to products and resources in the Online Sales channels storefront. Locksmith can be used to lock individual products or collections of products, and there's a location key condition, or domain/market key conditions that can be used to grant or block access to customers based on the location they are connecting from.\u0026nbsp;\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eI've included our guide on setting up a basic lock here, for reference: \u003ca href=\"https://www.locksmith.guide/basics/creating-locks\"\u003eCreating locks\u003c/a\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eThere are two ways to manage access your locks based on a customer's location:\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003col\u003e\u003cli\u003eWe have a location key condition - that checks the approximate location a customer is connecting from based on their IP address. Importantly, this\u0026nbsp;\u003ci\u003ewill\u003c/i\u003e\u0026nbsp;negatively affect SEO for locked content that isn't a variant, or using manual mode. Our guide on using this key condition is here:\u0026nbsp;\u003ca href=\"https://docs.uselocksmith.com/article/192-restricting-by-location\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eRestricting by a visitor's location\u003c/a\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eThe domain key or a Liquid key condition can be used to check for the market a customer is connecting from. This works with Shopify Markets in your store to either check the domain the customers are viewing. Or a Liquid lock can be used to check for a domain's subfolder, or the localisation object that the customer has been assigned. These keys won't prevent search engines from indexing that locked content for those regions:\u0026nbsp;\u003ca href=\"https://www.locksmith.guide/tutorials/more/shopify-markets\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eShowing content only to specific Markets\u003c/a\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ol\u003e\u003cbr\u003eIt's also worth noting here that Locksmith cannot restrict shipping locations. But Shopify does have some options for that:\u0026nbsp;\u003ca href=\"https://help.shopify.com/en/manual/shipping/setting-up-and-managing-your-shipping/shipping-profiles/setting-up-shipping-profiles#create-a-custom-shipping-profile\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eShopify's shipping profiles\u003c/a\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eLet me know if you have any questions about this. :)\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eCheers!\u003cbr\u003e-Tristan\u003cbr\u003e",
